a04c345b-4a10-5df6-9294-7bf403319ae3,tg:rubgr:689,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Harbour of Naples. Also for the ships [onleesbaar]. The same principle of presentation from the water with town on the background and ships etc. BM Add.MS 12531 [= Add. 12531: Genealogía del Infante Dom Fernando de Portugal, con miniaturas del flamenco Simon Bening hechas en Brujas y del lusitano António de Holanda, pintadas en Lisboa, según el plan de éste, 1530-34: Kren, no. 9, pp. 69-78], Illuminated Genealogy of the Portugese Royal Family, c. 1530. Some sheets painted by Simon Being at Bruges from designs probably by Antonio de Holanda, which had been sent from Lisbon; the remainder are by another artist perhaps by Antonio de Holanda himself. The views of Lisbon & Santarem points to local knowledge; [verso] ff. 7, 8 The royal family of Portugal ...below are views of Lisbon (f. 7) & Santarem (f. 8) ... In the river are seen (to the right) lateen-rigged caravels and (to the left) naos and oared galleys (Exhibition Catal. B.M. Prince Henry the Navigator and Portuguese Maritime Enterprise, Sept.-Oct. 1960, p. 3 f. (N° 5) Catal. adest.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Harbour of Naples. Also for the ships [onleesbaar]. The same principle of presentation from the water with town on the background and ships etc. BM Add.MS 12531 [= Add. 12531: Genealogía del Infante Dom Fernando de Portugal, con miniaturas del flamenco Simon Bening hechas en Brujas y del lusitano António de Holanda, pintadas en Lisboa, según el plan de éste, 1530-34: Kren, no. 9, pp. 69-78], Illuminated Genealogy of the Portugese Royal Family, c. 1530. Some sheets painted by Simon Being at Bruges from designs probably by Antonio de Holanda, which had been sent from Lisbon; the remainder are by another artist perhaps by Antonio de Holanda himself. The views of Lisbon & Santarem points to local knowledge; [verso] ff. 7, 8 The royal family of Portugal ...below are views of Lisbon (f. 7) & Santarem (f. 8) ... In the river are seen (to the right) lateen-rigged caravels and (to the left) naos and oared galleys (Exhibition Catal. B.M. Prince Henry the Navigator and Portuguese Maritime Enterprise, Sept.-Oct. 1960, p. 3 f. (N° 5) Catal. adest.</content>
